types of lambda expressions
1- no parameters, no return type
()->{} curly brace if there are multiple statement otherwise no need
()->System.out.println("hello");
()->{
    System.out.println("hello");
    System.out.println("hello");
    };


2- no parameter, with return value
()->{
     int n1=10,n2=20;
     return (n1+n2);
     };     
()-> 20;  if there is single line then no need to use return keyword or it will show error


3- one parameter with no return value
(int n)->System.out.println(n*n);
(n)->print(n*n);
n->print(n*n);
n->(n>10)?print("yes"):print("no");


4- one parameter with return value
(int num)->num*num;
(num)->num*num;
num->num*num;


5- multiple parameter no return value
(int a,int b)->print(a+b);
(a,b)->print(a+b);


6- multiple parameter with retun value
(int a,int b)->a+b;



